originalText.text: I found Meryl's highly detailed information on how to retrieve a birth certificate with Apostille on her website.  It was in the peak of Covid 19 and I needed to get this document ASAP.  I figured, leave it to the pro (I didn't want to make any mistakes and create unnecessary delays).  I contacted Meryl and she responded right away. She took care of it in less time then she estimated, and I'm sure much less time that it would have taken me.  I thought that her fees were very reasonable.  The process with her was easy and payment was easy.  I highly recommend her!

originalText.text: I was looking for a genealogist to help me discover where my grandfather was born.  He was an orphan, and no one was able to nail down the answer.  My father asked me to research it, and I spent a good bit of time looking for a definitive answer but came up empty.  I did a search to find a professional genealogist, and I came across this wonderful site with helpful blogs that were so well done. I looked around for a genealogist, but I always returned back to the We Go Way Back site.  I contacted Meryl, and she was so professional and I understood exactly how the process would work. I am a realist, so I knew that she might not be able to help me find my needle in a haystack.  Well...it was wonderful when she emailed me her report.  It was so thorough, and there was my answer.  I only wish that I had found her four years ago so that my dad would have had his answer.  It was the best thing that I did during the pandemic and worth every penny!

originalText.text: Genealogy research can be very difficult in New York City, especially if you are researching a common name. I was extremely pleased with the report that I received from Meryl that was on time, on budget and extremely well researched. Having a local expert like Meryl that knows how to navigate the numerous government record offices, as well as her strong historical knowledge of the city and its adjoining areas was critical to helping end some roadblocks that had stymied my research efforts for years. I highly recommend her services and plan on using them again in the near future.

originalText.text: I am preparing a book about a 19th century physician and Meryl's help has been invaluable in tracking down obscure data on where and how he lived. I highly recommend her. She kept me informed during her work, despite COVID, and delivered a trove of information from local records I could never have located on my own.
